Hi [~leftnoteasy]
Thank you very much for doing this work item. Its looking fine and useful.

Few comments initially.

1.
{code}
    Map<ApplicationAttemptId, Set<RMContainer>> toPreempt = null;
314	    for (PreemptionCandidatesSelector selectionPolicy :
315	        candidatesSelectionPolicies) {
316	      toPreempt = selectionPolicy.selectCandidates(toPreempt,
317	          clusterResources, totalPreemptionAllowed);
318	    }
{code}

I am not much getting much idea abt the use of having multiple policies. Bcz if one selected candidate from policy1 can  be vetoed by another policy (now we have only one), will it be tough to explain. Here multi layer filtering is what happening, will it be fine we can use one policy or a group of selected policy rather than looping all. Since we do not have a usecase now, i think its ok. But it will be great if you could share some info on same.

2. {{PreemptableResourceCalculator}} does not have much stateful information to keep or storing some stateful information
from premption round to round. So do we need to keep this object per PreemptionCandidatesSelector object. May be a generic one (static util class) is enough for whole PCPP?

- SchedulingEditPolicy interface should not be changed as it is pluggable
- remove PreemptableQueue#getKillableContainers(String partition) {
- why is the previous PCPP#cleanupStaledKillableContainers logic removed?

